{"ts":"2026-07-18T15:09:38.214Z","author":"codex-root","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-18T15:09:38.214Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-18T15:09:38.214Z","author":"codex-root","text":"GitHub intake 2026-07-18: GH-595 (https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/595) independently confirms the canonical lean-JSON scope: pm list --json spends about 44% of its envelope on null filter echoes. The report also adds a related pagination-envelope stability requirement (always-present total/has_more and removal of redundant has_more/truncated semantics). All-status duplicate search maps the null-bloat portion here; retain one canonical implementation lineage and account for the pagination addition when this item is claimed."}]}],"before_hash":"e64e921726481a84a7d133d8665f5796c4dd5b0be523ed2c80fb5c3dc45619df","after_hash":"f4e6ca1a58ebfc8b6bf31a1f9f1777a71ba02185361493d67349c2c48685787d"}
